<item>
            <title>[LANG-1089] FastDateParser does not handle excess hours as per SimpleDateFormat</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/LANG-1089</link>
                <project id="12310481" key="LANG">Commons Lang</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;FastDateParser does not do any validation of dates/times.&lt;br/&gt;
It acts similarly to SimpleDateFormat (SDF) in lenient mode.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;However it does not generate the same output as SDF for input where the number of hours is greater than the normal range (e.g. &amp;gt; 12 for hh or &amp;gt; 23 for HH)&lt;/p&gt;</description>
